'''Abé''' (also spelled '''Abbé''', '''Abbey''', '''Abi''') is a language of uncertain classification within the [[Kwa language|Kwa]] branch of the [[Niger–Congo languages|Niger–Congo]] family. It is spoken in [[Ivory Coast]].
The [[dialects]] of Abé are [[Tioffo]], [[Morie]], [[Abbey-Ve]], and [[Kos (dialect)|Kos]].
In 1995 there were estimated to be 170,000 speakers, primarily in the Department of Agboville.
