'''Jola''' ({{lang-fr|Diola}}; Jola: ''Joola''), also called '''Jola-Fonyi''' ({{lang-fr|Diola-Fogny}}), is a language spoken by half a million people in the [[Casamance]] region of [[Senegal]], and neighboring countries. Jola-Fonyi is one of several closely related [[Jola languages]] spoken in the area.

