'''Walter Steven DeKeseredy''' (born March 6, 1959)<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n91126757.html |title=DeKeseredy, Walter S., 1959- |website=Library of Congress Name Authority File |access-date=2018-09-06}}</ref> is the Anna Deane Carlson Endowed Chair of Social Sciences at [[West Virginia University]], where he is also director of the Research Center on Violence and professor of sociology. He received his Ph.D. from [[York University]] in 1988, and formerly taught at [[Carleton University]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://cjrc.osu.edu/people/walter.dekeseredy |title=Walter DeKeseredy |date=2012-10-03 |website=Criminal Justice Research Center |language=en |access-date=2018-09-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.macleans.ca/education/university/canadian-universities-are-failing-students-on-sexual-assault/ |title=Canadian universities are failing students on sexual assault |last=Schwartz |first=Zane |date=2018-03-01 |work=Macleans |access-date=2018-09-06 |language=en-US}}</ref> he is known for his research on [[violence against women]], which he has been studying for more than thirty years.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2016/05/when-a-classmate-is-a-former-inmate/480864/ |title=When a Classmate Is a Former Inmate |last=Lantigua-Williams |first=Juleyka |date=2016-05-05 |website=The Atlantic |language=en-US |access-date=2018-09-06}}</ref> In particular, he is known for studying the role of threats to [[masculinity]] in male violence against women.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.usnews.com/news/best-states/west-virginia/articles/2018-02-20/wvu-researcher-sees-shooter-status-threat-in-mass-killings |title=WVU Researcher Sees Shooter Status Threat in Mass Killings |last=Press |first=Associated |date=2018-02-20 |work=U.S. News & World Report |access-date=2018-09-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/life-style/life/73591708/we-need-to-talk-about-how-patriarchy-also-pressures-men-to-be-likeable |title=We need to talk about how patriarchy also pressures men to be 'likeable' |last=Reilly |first=Natalie |date=2015-11-02 |work=Stuff.co.nz |access-date=2018-09-06 |language=en}}</ref>
